message.content: cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.ET - The paper introduces a new reversible object-oriented programming language and provides a formalization of its semantics and type system. This makes it highly likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the implementation of the language and its computational universality, which could place it in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper describes techniques for garbage-free translation to a reversible assembly language, which could place it in the Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) sub-category.
